  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Mandragora</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>mandragora</abilityid>    
    <abilityranks from="1" to="4"/>
    <abilitycheck>
      <defaults>pool_cost_1</defaults>
      <actiontype><minor/></actiontype>
      <critsuccess></critsuccess>
      <critfail></critfail>
      <!-- <boon></boon> -->
      <!-- <indifferent>1</indifferent> -->
      <!-- <bane></bane> -->
      <range><na/></range>
      <keywords><magicpool/></keywords>
      <dc>11</dc>
    </abilitycheck>
    <prereqabilityrank>wild-magic_2</prereqabilityrank>
    <spline></spline>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	If the character has access to a tree root, turnip <etc/> the
	character can infuse it with an evil spirit for a short an 10+Rank minutes.
	The animated Mandragora behaves like a small servant and will perform
	actions as directed by the caster.  The Mandragora is malevolent and
	will attempt to misconstrue instructions in such a way as to allow it
	to hurt others.
      </p>

      <p>
	In a fight the Mandragora has HP: 5, Defence: 15, and attacks automatically
	for 1 hp of biting damage each round.  If the Mandragora is made from
	an actual mandragora root then the creature has HP: 9 and does 2 HP damage
	per round.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>    
  </ability> 
  


  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Therianthropy</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>magic.therianthropy</abilityid>    
    <abilityranks from="1" to="4"/>
    <abilitycheck>
      <defaults>pool_cost_2</defaults>
      <actiontype><minor/></actiontype>
      <critsuccess></critsuccess>
      <critfail></critfail>
      <!-- <boon></boon> -->
      <!-- <indifferent>2</indifferent> -->
      <!-- <bane></bane> -->
      <range><na/></range>
      <!-- <keywords><magicpool/></keywords> -->
      <dc>11</dc>
    </abilitycheck>
    <prereqabilityrank>hyperosmia_2</prereqabilityrank>
    <spline><p x="0" y="30"/></spline>
    <abilitydescription>
      <indexentry>Shapeshifting<subentry>see Therianthropy</subentry></indexentry>
      <figure position="h">
        <img id="dore_therianthropy" scale="0.6"/>
      </figure>
      
      <p>
	The caster takes animal form for up to a few hours.  The first
	time the caster casts the spell they roll on the appropriate Therianthropy
	table to choose the animal to which they are atuned.  	That is the animal
	that they will always change into when casting this spell.  It should be
	noted that therianthropy is a very different thing from lycanthropy.
      </p>

      <table>
	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
	<tablespec><fixed>0.2</fixed><fixed>0.7</fixed></tablespec>
	<tabletitle>Therianthropy Temperate Table</tabletitle>
	<tablelabel>fig:therianthropy</tablelabel>

	<tableheaderrow>
	  <td>Roll d88</td>
	  <td>Animal</td>
	</tableheaderrow>

	<tablerow> <td>11</td><td>Cockroach</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>12</td><td>Beetle</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>13-14</td><td>House fly or Firefly</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>15-18</td><td>Spider</td></tablerow>

	<tablerow> <td>21-25</td><td>Frog, Toad, Lizard or Newt</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>26-27</td><td>Squirrel, Mouse, Mole or Hedgehog</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>28</td><td>Hare or Rabbit</td></tablerow>
	
	<tablerow> <td>31</td><td>Goat or Ibex</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>32-34</td><td>Sparrow, Crow, or Pidgeon</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>35-36</td><td>Weasel, Polecat or Ferret</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>37-38</td><td>Bat</td></tablerow>

	<tablerow> <td>41-42</td><td>Yak, Musk Ox, Bison</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>43-44</td><td>Deer, Reindeer, or Elk</td></tablerow>
	<tablerow> <td>45-46</td><td>Pig or Wild Boar</td></tablerow>	
	<tablerow> <td>47-48</td><td>Horse</td></tablerow>
	
	<tablerow> <td>51-52</td><td>Fox or Jackal</td></tablerow>
