  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Vermin Swarm</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>vermin_swarm</abilityid>    
    <abilityranks from="1" to="4"/>
    <abilitycheck>
      <defaults>pool_cost_1</defaults>
      <actiontype><minor/></actiontype>
      <critsuccess></critsuccess>
      <critfail></critfail>
      <!-- <boon></boon> -->
      <!-- <indifferent>1</indifferent> -->
      <!-- <bane></bane> -->
      <range><na/></range>
      <!-- <keywords><magicpool/></keywords> -->
      <dc>7</dc>
    </abilitycheck>
    <prereqabilityrank>wild-magic_1</prereqabilityrank>
    <spline><p x="-45" y="30"/></spline>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	The character summons a swarm of vermin.  The GM should choose one 
	of the following types of swarms either randomly or as appropriate to
	the context: Spiders, Beetles, Rats, Bees, Flys, Bats, Ravens, Maggots.
	Swarms remain in play until the end of combat.   If there are no vermin
	in the vicinity then none can be summoned.  The caster can sense the
	presence of vermin before attempting to cast this spell.
      </p>

      <table>
	<tablecategory>Standard</tablecategory>
	<tablespec><fixed>0.3</fixed><fixed>0.6</fixed></tablespec>
	<tabletitle>Vermin Swarm Overcharge Table</tabletitle>
	<tablelabel>fig:vermin-swarm-overcharge</tablelabel>

	<tableheaderrow>
	  <td>Roll d88</td>
	  <td>Overcharge Effect</td>
	</tableheaderrow>

	<tablerow>
	  <td>11-28</td>
	  <td>The swarm mistakes the caster for the target.  They GM moves the swarm
	  towards the caster each turn until they are destroyed </td>
	</tablerow>

	<tablerow>
	  <td>31-38</td>
	  <td>The casters mind is linked to the swarm.  They can either banish the swarm
	  or control it, but that is all.
	  </td>
	</tablerow>

	<tablerow>
	  <td>41-58</td>
	  <td>Something from beyond takes a big bite out of the caster.  Caster suffers
	  3d6 damage.</td>
	</tablerow>

	<tablerow>
	  <td>61-88</td>
	  <td>Weirdness ensues.. Reroll on the Overcharge Effects Table..</td>
	</tablerow>
      </table>      
    </abilitydescription>
  </ability>

  
