  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Warp Wood</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>warp_wood</abilityid>
    <abilityranks from="1" to="4"/>
    <abilitycheck>
      <defaults>pool_cost_1</defaults>
      <actiontype><minor/></actiontype>
      <critsuccess></critsuccess>
      <critfail></critfail>
      <!-- <boon></boon> -->
      <!-- <bane></bane> -->
      <range><na/></range>
      <!-- <keywords><magicpool/></keywords> -->
      <!-- <indifferent>1</indifferent> -->
      <dc>11</dc>
    </abilitycheck>
    <prereqabilityrank>wild-magic_1</prereqabilityrank>
    <spline><p x="-60" y="0"/></spline>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	The caster can warp wood at a distance.  This spell can be used
	to warp a wooden door.. rendering it unclosable if it was open at the
	time of casting, or unopenable if it was shut at the time of casting.
	It can render a quiver of arrows extremely inaccurate, -6 to hit, or
	destroy a bow.
      </p>

      <p>
	The spell has a range of <measurement><metric>30m</metric>
	<imperial>100'</imperial></measurement>. The spell can effect one
	item For each rank of the spell.  The spells abilities linger on the
	character.. they cast the spell, and then they can choose which items
	to warp anytime as a free action over the next five minutes/30 turns. 
      </p>	
    </abilitydescription>    
  </ability>
